			<description><![CDATA[<p>
	<strong>Overview of Swapit</strong></p>
<p>
	Swapit is the UK&#39;s leading trading site for children and teenagers. It works a little bit like eBay or Nectar, allowing teens and children to trade items they&rsquo;ve grown out of or no longer want for a virtual currency called Swapits. Swapit is also a leading provider of research and insight on the youth market.<br />
	Advertising and marketing partners include major blue-chip clients such as Disney, Warner Brothers, LEGO, Universal Music and many others.<br />
	Our Central London Office is filled with young, ambitious and vibrant people in their twenties and thirties.<br />
	Our investors comprise well-known VC funds and seasoned internet investors who have backed companies such as Facebook, Linked-in and Betfair.</p>
<p>
	<br />
	<strong>The role</strong></p>
<p>
	At Swapit you will be challenged constantly as we seek to delight and excite a very young, energetic and demanding audience &ndash; UK kids and teens.</p>
<p>
	Key objectives of the role:</p>
<ul>
	<li>
		Optimisation of existing website&nbsp; and services through analysis</li>
	<li>
		Site structure map creation and monitoring</li>
	<li>
		Progress reporting on stats&ndash; preparation and optimisation of weekly and monthly KPI reports</li>
	<li>
		Social media strategy and implementationEmail marketing &ndash; working with designers to develop effective emails, then tracking email performance to drive up new users.</li>
	<li>
		Online advertising through social networks and Google</li>
	<li>
		User testing to improve product performance</li>
</ul>
<p>
	The responsibilities of the role will include:</p>
<ul>
	<li>
		Optimisation of existing applications and services based on data analysis</li>
	<li style="margin-left: 40px;">
		Using Google Analytics and KISSmetrics to monitor page performance and thus deliver improvements to campaigns and site performance improvements</li>
	<li style="margin-left: 40px;">
		Monitor stats on the database and define stats to collect</li>
	<li style="margin-left: 40px;">
		Investigating CTR and methods of optimisation for community proposition to succeed &ndash; enable us to offer advice to partners on how to improve their CTR&rsquo;s</li>
	<li>
		User journey mapping</li>
	<li style="margin-left: 40px;">
		The creation and upkeep of a &#39;map&#39; showing user journeys and decision points through the site</li>
	<li style="margin-left: 40px;">
		Optimising site structure with respect to user journeys</li>
	<li>
		Progress reporting on KPI data</li>
	<li style="margin-left: 40px;">
		Monitor weekly progress and report to team in Monday meeting</li>
	<li>
		&bull; Social media strategy</li>
	<li style="margin-left: 40px;">
		Develop and implement social media strategy</li>
	<li style="margin-left: 40px;">
		Engage users through social media &ndash; meeting specified targets</li>
	<li style="margin-left: 40px;">
		Work closely with copywriter to deliver interesting and engaging content</li>
	<li style="margin-left: 40px;">
		Keep page fresh and up-to-date</li>
	<li style="margin-left: 40px;">
		Competitor analysis on Facebook and Twitter</li>
	<li style="margin-left: 40px;">
		Blog analysis</li>
	<li>
		&bull; Email marketing</li>
	<li style="margin-left: 40px;">
		Work with Email Vision (&ldquo;EMV&rdquo;, our email service provider) and web designers to create engaging newsletters which deliver high CTR&rsquo;s</li>
	<li style="margin-left: 40px;">
		Improve &ldquo;dormant user&rdquo; email marketing and knowledge of why users are becoming dormant</li>
	<li style="margin-left: 40px;">
		Investigate ways to create faster and simpler templates to send emails</li>
	<li style="margin-left: 40px;">
		Improve targeting of emails through gaining knowledge of mailshot programme EMV.</li>
	<li>
		&bull; Online advertising through social networks and Google</li>
	<li style="margin-left: 40px;">
		Manage advertising on Facebook and the conversion to sign-up</li>
	<li style="margin-left: 40px;">
		Manage Google Adwords and see what converts</li>
	<li style="margin-left: 40px;">
		Improve Customer Acquisition processes to bring more users to Swapit!</li>
	<li>
		&bull; User testing</li>
	<li style="margin-left: 40px;">
		Test product on real users, liase with schools to set up focus groups and take Swapit into classes</li>
	<li style="margin-left: 40px;">
		Organise sessions in Swapit where kids come to test products and everything that goes with that i.e. transport, parental approval</li>
	<li style="margin-left: 40px;">
		Aid Market Research department in better integrating our research panel within the Swapit site and improve the performance of this feature</li>
	<li style="margin-left: 40px;">
		Management of SnapEngage/UserVoice to obtain / analyse user feedback</li>
	<li style="margin-left: 40px;">
		Using KISSinsights effectively to run tests</li>
</ul>
<p>
	<strong>Skills</strong></p>
<p>
	<br />
	The company is a small business in a growth market with a lot to do in a short space of time. The successful candidate needs to be a self starter, logical thinker with drive and discipline to get things done, a genuine team player, happy to deal with granular detail as well as bigger picture product development.</p>
<p>
	<br />
	Skills required:</p>
<ul>
	<li>
		2:1 final grade in a Science, Engineering, Maths or numerical degree, ideally from a top tier university, and preferably with some prior work experience in a B2C marketing role.</li>
	<li>
		Hard-working, driven and committed to going the extra mile to deliver great quality work.</li>
	<li>
		Well-organised as you&rsquo;ll be juggling several projects at once so you&rsquo;ll need to have a&nbsp; methodical approach to project management and use some proven techniques for staying on top of your task list.</li>
	<li>
		Creative, a good eye for design and lots of fresh ideas to improve the way we do things.</li>
	<li>
		Detail-focused and a hawk eye for typos and small details.</li>
	<li>
		Passionate about the internet and user of social media, forums, blogs.</li>
	<li>
		Passionate about marketing, enthusiastic and hungry to learn and develop a career in marketing</li>
	<li>
		Tech savvy, creative thinker with passion for working with web 2.0 and mobile 2.0 applications.</li>
	<li>
		Ability to work across functions to deliver initiatives and manage external suppliers/contractors as required.</li>
	<li>
		Ability to document requirements, analysis and definition for internal and third party specifications and briefings.</li>
	<li>
		A &lsquo;can-do&rsquo; mentality demonstrating a real passion for making things happen, combined with a flexible approach, reflecting the dynamic nature of the role and the business.</li>
	<li>
		Interest in uncovering and using customer insight to drive change and innovation.</li>
</ul>
<p>
	Although this is an entry-level position, it is a tremendous learning opportunity for an ambitious and motivated individual.</p>
